overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed Statement of Work and questionnaire specification. The
  agent performed a comprehensive analysis, identifying several critical gaps in
  the existing implementation. Subsequently, the agent proceeded to implement
  the identified missing features. This included adding a 1-10 severity scale
  for tiredness interference, complete with safety warnings for high scores. The
  agent also integrated detection logic and corresponding recommendations for
  Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome.
  Furthermore, a new section was added to the report and PDF for placeholder
  outbound links to relevant sleep and mental health resources. Finally, a
  weighted scoring mechanism for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) was
  implemented, enhancing the accuracy of its detection. All changes were applied
  to both the interactive report and the PDF generation.
